meanings.definition: To handle too much or too often.
meanings.sent1: She overhandled the fragile vase, causing it to break.
meanings.sent2: The teacher warned the students not to overhandle the classroom pets.
meanings.sent3: After overhandling the dough, it became tough and chewy.
meanings.sent4: The delicate fabric tore easily from overhandling.
meanings.sent5: Overhandling the electronic device may lead to malfunctions.

meanings.sent1: The overhandling of the antique book damaged its pages.
meanings.sent2: The overhandling of evidence can compromise a crime scene.
meanings.sent3: The overhandling of the situation only made things more complicated.
meanings.sent4: The overhandling of the fragile artifact led to its destruction.
meanings.sent5: Avoid overhandling delicate items to prevent damage.
